more, the mismatch count is huge. Looking at the `stimulus_gen` task `reset_test`, it manipulates `reset` and checks `tb_match`. If the testbench's reset sequence or its verification of the reset type is incorrect, it will trigger mismatches or incorrect hints. \n10. Given the high mismatch rate and the specific hint regarding reset type (which contradicts the RTL implementation), the testbench's verification logic (specifically the `reset_test` task or the way it drives the reset) is the most likely culprit for the simulation failure.",
